From 912027cecd739d17fe34b062e7122554dda96f53 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mikhail-Za <86077672+Mikhail-Za@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 15:53:58 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] T-Display P4: default bluetooth.enabled=false when BT is
 excluded

On MESHTASTIC_EXCLUDE_BLUETOOTH builds (T-Display P4 dual-boot), a fresh
config defaulted bluetooth.enabled=true (the T-Display P4 is not in NodeDB's
BT-off-by-default board list), which forces the on-screen MUI client into a
dead-end Bluetooth "programming mode" screen every boot. Default it off when
Bluetooth is compiled out.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/mesh/NodeDB.cpp | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/mesh/NodeDB.cpp b/src/mesh/NodeDB.cpp
index ac724e5e0..850be9061 100644
--- a/src/mesh/NodeDB.cpp
+++ b/src/mesh/NodeDB.cpp
@@ -934,6 +934,11 @@ void NodeDB::installDefaultConfig(bool preserveKey = false)
     HAS_TFT
     // switch BT off by default; use TFT programming mode or hotkey to enable
     config.bluetooth.enabled = false;
+#elif defined(MESHTASTIC_EXCLUDE_BLUETOOTH)
+    // BT is compiled out of this build (T-Display P4 dual-boot) -> never default it on,
+    // or PacketAPI (runOnce) traps the MUI in a dead-end Bluetooth "programming mode"
+    // screen on every fresh config. (Recovered Unit B 2026-06-17 by setting it off.)
+    config.bluetooth.enabled = false;
 #else
     // default to bluetooth capability of platform as default
     config.bluetooth.enabled = true;
-- 
2.53.0.windows.2

